    "As shown in Table 3, models trained with RT methods exhibit smaller reductions in clean accuracy.",
    "However, their AR degrades significantly, with performance dropping to nearly zero under strong attacks such as C&W and Auto-Attack.",
    "Only the CVaR method achieves non-zero AR performance against PGD attacks, though it still lags behind models trained with AT methods.",
    "A similar observation is evident in Fig. 2 (a), where RT methods consistently appear along the leftmost vertical axis, indicating near-zero AR performance across all datasets and models.",
    "More results are shown in Table 9."
